        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-15T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-15T13:00:00-05:00" n="444" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/8–1445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Australia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Minter</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-15T14:00:00-04:00">August 15, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. You should inform the Dominion Government that under the plan of surrender
                    which has been arranged, the Japanese troops in Burma, Thailand, Malaya, Borneo,
                    Netherlands Indies, New Guinea, the Bismarcks, and Solomons are to surrender to
                    the Supreme Commander, Southeast Asia Command, or to the Australian Command, and
                    suggest that it may wish to consult with Lord Mountbatten with a view to
                    arrangements as to the specific areas where the Australian Command will accept
                    the surrender.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
